quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  40,38,"And the man who believed urged, ‚ÄúO my people! Follow me, ňĻandňļ I will lead you to the Way of Guidance"
  40,39,"O my people! This worldly life is only ňĻa fleetingňļ enjoyment, whereas the Hereafter is truly the home of settlement"
  40,40,"Whoever does an evil deed will only be paid back with its equivalent. And whoever does good, whether male or female, and is a believer, they will enter Paradise, where they will be provided for without limit"
  40,41,"O my people! How is it that I invite you to salvation, while you invite me to the Fire"
  40,42,"You invite me to disbelieve in Allah and associate with Him what I have no knowledge of, while I invite you to the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  40,43,"There is no doubt that whatever ňĻidolsňļ you invite me to ňĻworshipňļ are not worthy to be invoked either in this world or the Hereafter.¬†ňĻUndoubtedly,ňļ our return is to Allah, and the transgressors will be the inmates of the Fire"
  40,44,"You will remember what I say to you, and I entrust my affairs to Allah. Surely Allah is All-Seeing of all ňĻHisňļ servants.‚ÄĚ"
  40,45,So Allah protected him from the evil of their schemes. And Pharaoh‚Äôs people were overwhelmed by an evil punishment
  40,46,"they are exposed to the Fire ňĻin their gravesňļ morning and evening. And on the Day the Hour will be established ňĻit will be saidňļ, ‚ÄúAdmit Pharaoh‚Äôs people into the harshest punishment ňĻof Hellňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  40,47,"ňĻConsider the Dayňļ when they will dispute in the Fire, and the lowly ňĻfollowersňļ will appeal to the arrogant ňĻleadersňļ, ‚ÄúWe were your ňĻdedicatedňļ followers, will you then shield us from a portion of the Fire?‚ÄĚ"
  40,48,"The arrogant will say, ‚ÄúWe are all in it! ňĻForňļ Allah has already passed judgment over ňĻHisňļ servants.‚ÄĚ"
  40,49,"And those in the Fire will cry out to the keepers of Hell,¬†‚ÄúPray to your Lord to lighten the torment for us ňĻevenňļ for one day!‚ÄĚ"
  40,50,"The keepers will reply, ‚ÄúDid your messengers not ňĻconstantlyňļ come to you with clear proofs?‚ÄĚ They will say, ‚ÄúYes ňĻthey didňļ.‚ÄĚ The keepers will say, ‚ÄúThen pray! Though the prayer of the disbelievers is only in vain.‚ÄĚ"